    "causal_summary": "The `system-skill-advisor/mcp_server` vitest suite reported 61 of 553 tests failing in the working tree. The dominant cause was the committed deep-loop merge (`ce9e313e7f`), which folded the five legacy deep-loop skills (`deep-context`, `deep-research`, `deep-review`, `deep-ai-council`, `deep-improvement`) into one merged skill `deep-loop-workflows`, but left scorer fixtures, corpora, ledgers, the Python disambiguation layer, and the metadata-category allowlist still expecting the now-deleted legacy skill ids. Separately, an intentional `GOVERNOR_DIRECTIVE` capsule appended to every advisor brief in `lib/render.ts` broke ~15 brief-assertion tests that hard-coded the pre-governor brief string. After those 26 were fixed, 36 failures remained in two files: the settings-parity guard read the gitignored machine-local `.claude/settings.local.json` (which carries no hooks) instead of the committed `.claude/settings.json`, and the graph-health validator failed on three edge-symmetry asymmetries in external skill metadata.",
